Hascol Petroleum 
 

 


 



Hascol Petroleum 



Jun 10,2014 | 6:48 PM PKT 


Client Industry: Energy UtilitiesProject Overview: Hascol Petroleum Limited (HPL) is a growing Oil Marketing company in Pakistan was in search of an ERP solution to automate core operations of an oil marketing company and powerful enough to generate various management reports for better decision making. HPL, after evaluating SAP, Oracle EBS and Microsoft Dynamics AX, had chosen JD Edwards EnterpriseOne ERP suite and Systems Ltd as implementation partner. Successful implementation of JD Edwards has helped HPL in meeting many immediate goals while laying solid foundation for future growth. Modules implemented in HPL are:
JD Edwards Financials Management
Sales Order Management
Advanced Pricing
Procurement Management
Inventory Management
Bulk Stock Management
Transportation Management
HPL has divided their operation in four line of business i.e Retail, Hi-Street, Lubricants and Industrial business. It is required to monitor profitability by line of business, by customer and by product. To cater their reporting needs a unique organizational structure is designed in JD Edwards. This structure includes four notational companies with respect to line of business which are consolidated in one parent company i.e Hascol Petroleum. To monitor petrol pump wise profitability a unique Business Unit is associated with each petrol which results in complete visibility in terms of cost and revenue. 
Bulk Stock Management is designed specifically for Oil & Gas Industry that handles the entire downstream bulk product supply and demand complexities. Our proposed solution enabled HPL to:
Control all types of product movement, including intra-depot stock movements, such as tank-to-tank transfers, re-brands, decanting, blending, and filling.
Pinpoint inventory gains and losses before they become significant with flexible reconciliation capabilities.
Automatically record inventory gains and losses occurs due to temperature variations.
Project Status: CompletedProposed Solution: Oracle JD Edwards EnterpriseOnePriority: 1

 




